                            <comment id="14102961" author="chutium" created="Tue, 19 Aug 2014 22:29:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;be careful if someone is working on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-2551&quot; title=&quot;Cleanup FilteringParquetRowInputFormat&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-2551&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-2551&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, make sure the new change passes test case &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;test(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Read a parquet file instead of a directory&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14102967" author="apachespark" created="Tue, 19 Aug 2014 22:32:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;User &apos;chutium&apos; has created a pull request for this issue:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/2044&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/2044&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14102979" author="chutium" created="Tue, 19 Aug 2014 22:41:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;after this PR, we can pass the full path of a parquet file instead of the path of directory to sqlContext.parquetFile&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;given a path of a non parquet file, will throw a RuntimeException:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;scala&amp;gt; val readFile = sqlContext.parquetFile(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;/tmp/people.txt&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)
java.lang.RuntimeException: file:/tmp/people.txt is not a Parquet file. expected magic number at tail [80, 65, 82, 49] but found [44, 50, 52, 10]
        at parquet.hadoop.ParquetFileReader.readFooter(ParquetFileReader.java:288)
        at org.apache.spark.sql.parquet.ParquetTypesConverter$$anonfun$readMetaData$3.apply(ParquetTypes.scala:391)
        at org.apache.spark.sql.parquet.ParquetTypesConverter$$anonfun$readMetaData$3.apply(ParquetTypes.scala:391)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
